subSubSection.paragraph:
Color in alcohol.
Body usually dark brown with evenly spaced small white dots; chin with scattered pigment; underparts from chin to anus and ventrals unpigmented; pectoral fin pigmented lightly (
Mees, 1974: 86
). Dorsal fin with dark base and irregular spots; caudal fin usually with whitish spots irregularly distributed over lobes (
Fig. 22
).

